{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The content passed to the summary-generation step includes data retrieved from all three sources.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is module handoff: three source clients -> aggregator -> summary input payload. A unit test of one formatter/parser would miss missing-source wiring bugs. Real OS/network is not required because stubs/fakes for the three sources can expose omission/merge defects. Higher levels rejected: System is disqualified by behavior text focusing on \"content passed\" (not real transport conditions); Agentic/Workflow are disqualified because this behavior does not depend on model output quality or multi-agent sequencing.","test_description":"Wire real collection/aggregation modules together with three controlled source fakes, execute one report build, and assert the exact summary-generation input contains all three source sections/fields.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.78,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When one data source is unavailable, the report is produced with a `data unavailable` note for that section rather than aborting.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is cross-module error propagation and fallback rendering (source adapter failure -> report assembler behavior). Unit is too low because the real defect appears at the boundary between fetch and report composition. System is rejected because a simulated unavailable source (timeout/exception) in-process can reproduce the failure mode needed by the behavior. Agentic/Workflow are disqualified by behavior text: requirement is fallback note/continuation, not model judgment.","test_description":"Run report generation with two normal source fakes and one failing fake (exception/timeout). Assert process completes, report includes `data unavailable` for only that section, and no global abort occurs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.09,"Integration":0.8,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The narrative summary accurately represents the key values present in the input data.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on generated narrative content quality (whether key values are faithfully represented). Deterministic stubs would mask real model misrepresentation/hallucination failures. Workflow is rejected because behavior specifies one summary-generation judgment, not multiple agentic decisions chained across stages.","test_description":"Run the real summary-generation model on representative weekly datasets and assert factual consistency against key-value checks (e.g., extracted numbers/issues/deploy counts match source data) across repeated runs/tolerances.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.8,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A complete report — from data collection through email delivery — reaches the configured recipient's inbox correctly.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Behavior explicitly requires end-to-end delivery to a real inbox, crossing network/email service boundaries and full process wiring. In-process mocks can hide real SMTP/API/auth/delivery path failures. Agentic is rejected because pass criterion is inbox delivery of complete report, not evaluating model decision quality; Workflow is rejected because no multi-agent decision chain is specified.","test_description":"Execute the scheduled script (or equivalent full run) against reachable test instances/services and a real test mailbox, then verify the email is received by configured recipients with expected report structure/content sections.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.09,"System":0.83,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the email delivery service is unreachable, the generated report is saved to a local file and delivery is retried on the next scheduled run.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Failure spans real infrastructure boundaries: unreachable email service plus durable local-file fallback across run boundaries/scheduling. Mocks often miss filesystem persistence, path/permission, and cross-run retry state defects. Agentic/Workflow are disqualified by behavior text, which is transport resilience and retry semantics, not model-output quality or multi-agent reasoning.","test_description":"Run 1: force real email endpoint failure/unreachability, assert report is persisted to local fallback file. Run 2 (next scheduled invocation with email restored): assert persisted report is retried/sent and fallback state is cleared/updated appropriately.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.14,"System":0.81,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.02}}]}
